HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 764
By Doggett
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Clara Parker of Giles
County.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to specially recognize
those estimable public servants who have dedicated themselves to improving the quality of life
for their fellow citizens; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Clara Parker, who has devoted forty years of her life
to the preservation and safeguarding of Giles County's historical records; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Parker co-founded the Giles County Archives in 1986 with her friend
and colleague Elizabeth White, establishing one of Tennessee's pioneering rural archives and
creating a lasting institution dedicated to preserving the history, records, and stories of Giles
County for future generations; and
WHEREAS, through meticulous effort, Clara Parker preserved thousands of historical
records by cleaning, cataloging, and organizing materials, while dedicating countless hours to
assisting individuals with genealogical research and guiding families in the compilation of family
history books that document personal stories and lineages; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Parker authored the Giles County Cemetery Book, a project requiring
years of research and extensive travel throughout the county to personally visit and document
each cemetery; she uncovered critical historical insights, including evidence that county records
were hidden during the Civil War to protect them from destruction; and
WHEREAS, Clara Parker strengthened archival preservation by building enduring
partnerships with local government, libraries, historical societies, and the Tennessee State
Library and Archives, advocating for best practices and for the preservation of records on
microfilm to ensure their long-term protection and accessibility; and
